OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F424A1773765957
OL,3,CPublic to decide which artist should
OL,4,Ccreate work from Sycamore Gap tree wood
OL,6,FThe public is being invited to vote on
OL,7,Fwhich of six shortlisted artists
OL,8,Fshould create an artwork from the wood
OL,9,Fof the illegally felled Sycamore Gap
OL,10,Ftree.
OL,12,FIn September, the National Trust
OL,13,Fcalled on artists, organisations and
OL,14,Fcreative agencies across the country
OL,15,Fto present ideas for a commission that
OL,16,Fhelps shape the tree's next chapter by
OL,17,Fusing half of its timber.
OL,19,FThe public ballot opens on Saturday 14
OL,20,FMarch, with voting running until
OL,21,Fmidnight on 28 March.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G1/9
