PN,42402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F424A1773765957
OL,3,CPublic to decide which artist should
OL,4,Ccreate work from Sycamore Gap tree wood
OL,6,FPeople will be able to select from the
OL,7,Fsix different visions for how the
OL,8,Ftree's story, symbolism and memory can
OL,9,Flive on for future generations.
OL,11,FThe public's input will contribute to
OL,12,F30% of the final decision, while
OL,13,Fscores from a judging panel made up of
OL,14,Fnature and art experts will make up
OL,15,F70%.
OL,17,FShortlisted proposals include ideas
OL,18,Fthat transform the Sycamore Gap tree
OL,19,Fwood into new artworks and sculptural
OL,20,Finstallations.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
