PN,42407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F424A1773765957
OL,3,CPublic to decide which artist should
OL,4,Ccreate work from Sycamore Gap tree wood
OL,6,F"It became more than a tree; it became
OL,7,Fpart of the emotional landscape of the
OL,8,Fnation.
OL,10,F"Each of the six proposals honours the
OL,11,Ftree in a different way, and we want
OL,12,Fpeople to choose the idea that
OL,13,Fcaptures what the Sycamore Gap tree
OL,14,Fmeant to them," she said.
OL,16,FSarah Munro, CEO/Creative Director at
OL,17,FBALTIC Centre for Contemporary Art in
OL,18,FNewcastle and member of the judging
OL,19,Fpanel, said: "Sycamore Gap has long
OL,20,Fbeen a symbol of connection`between
OL,21,Fpeople, place, and memory.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUvD@OO]{D@NOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/9
